title: For Sale:  Hanwei Practical Plus Elite Katana
postcontent:
I acquired this sword to have a practical sword with very good cutting  capabilities, but have never used it for cutting. I have used it for 'live' Iaido exercises however I acquired another sword for that purpose before I had the chance to use this one. I have periodically removed the sword to clean it; other than that it has been on display in my house. The Sword weights 2lb 7oz. The blade is forged and differentially hardened (HRC60 edge, HRC40 back) and the hamon is prominent but etched. The Practical Plus Elite features genuine Rayskin on the Tsuka with a tightly-woven Tsuka-Ito. The long tang is double-pegged for security. The blade is traditionally proportioned to appeal to the collector but it will also perform well in general cutting of hard or soft targets. The blade length is 28.5", handle is 11.5", and point of balance is at 5 1/2". The width at guard is 1.39", at tip is 1.03", thickness at guard 0.26" and thickness at tip 0.16". The Sori is 3/4".  The fittings of the Practical Plus are decorated in a Japanese Dogwood motif with dragon menuki, and the handsome Tsuba is of an iron “sunburst” design with a brass habaki. There are a lot of names for this type of tsuba (sunburst, wheel,….) and it’s claimed by Hanwei to be an old, original tsuba (museum piece). 

The sword also comes with a cleaning kit with the sword cleaning elements. The box was cracked, but I re-glued it.

The sword and cleaning kit ship separately to keep the cost of shipping down. The beginning cost is set at $325 to help cover the cost of shipping both items.
